1
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:52,120
Who took my child?!

2
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,240
Help me!

3
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,840
This house is haunted.

4
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:11,920
Then why doesn't the ghost
haunt anyone else? Why only you?

5
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,880
Mr. Narathon.

6
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:17,680
<i>The time has come.</i>
<i>No matter how hard you try to stop it,</i>

7
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:20,120
they are destined to meet.

8
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:32,600
Mook, go check on Dara.
She's been upstairs for quite a while.

9
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,760
Okay, Mom.

10
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,600
Are you feeling better now?

11
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,400
Whose house is this?

12
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:01,920
It's Dad's house. Don't you remember?

13
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:13,640
Maybe you should take her to sit down.

14
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,800
Okay.

15
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,600
Have you all
lived in this house for a long time?

16
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,400
You mean this house?

17
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:53,200
I only finished building this house
three years ago.

18
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,480
Why do you ask?

19
00:05:58,360 --> 00:06:00,160
Has anyone seen a child…?

20
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,520
Uh…

21
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,280
A little boy?

22
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:10,840
What are you talking about?
I don't understand.

23
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:15,720
What's wrong with you?
Why are you talking like this?

24
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:21,600
I think you should take her to rest.

25
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:27,440
Da, let's go rest.

26
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,640
No. I'm not going! No!

27
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:36,080
Calm down, Da. What's wrong?

28
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,480
Tell me.

29
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:38,840
Da.

30
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,400
Da.

31
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,440
Da.

32
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,840
- Da.
- Da.

33
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:44,720
- Da, what's wrong?
- Da.

34
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:48,560
Help! Da fainted.

35
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,480
- Da.
- Da.

36
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,800
Da.

37
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:41,600
Da, how are you feeling?

38
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,960
There's a ghost here.

39
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,800
- I can't stay here anymore.
- Da,

40
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,880
where are you going?
You're still not well yet.

41
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,520
Let's go, Na.

42
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,320
Run, Na.

43
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:20,520
Hurry up, Na.

44
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:24,200
Start the car.

45
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,360
Na, Na.

46
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:30,800
Drive carefully.

47
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,400
Oh?

48
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:39,440
Da looks strange.

49
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:42,200
Right. She asked questions

50
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:45,840
like she didn't know anything.
But when we were building the house,

51
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,520
she came with us all the time.

52
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:50,640
That's weird.

53
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:55,960
But she should be okay now.
Going back to Bangkok might help.

54
00:08:57,520 --> 00:09:00,800
- I'm sorry about this.
- It's okay.

55
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,680
I should probably head back too.

56
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:05,720
Are you going back to Bangkok too?

57
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,600
No.

58
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:11,040
I've been staying at the fish farm house
near the temple lately.

59
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:15,400
Oh, good. Then let the driver take you.
No need to walk all that way.

60
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,720
Thank you.

61
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:25,480
Excuse me. Ma'am?

62
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:30,760
My child.

63
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:36,040
Where are you, my child? Where are you?

64
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,200
- My child.
- Hey.

65
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:41,200
Are you alright?

66
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,800
Where's my child?!

67
00:13:56,960 --> 00:14:01,000
I checked everything. Every photo you sent

68
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:03,160
is still there.

69
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,680
- Are you sure?
- I think so.

70
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:14,040
Hey, wait.

71
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:15,160
<i>What?</i>

72
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,560
Looks like some photos are missing.

73
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,360
<i>How can you tell?</i>

74
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:26,640
The file numbers skip.

75
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,320
Six photos disappeared.

76
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:36,360
Hey, buddy. How about this?

77
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:39,320
<i>I'll check again when I get home.</i>

78
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:41,240
I'll keep you updated.

79
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:04,320
I'm out.

80
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,960
Failed again. As always.

81
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:12,320
But the new owner wasn't there.

82
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:16,920
There are plenty of ways
to track down a landowner.

83
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,280
I think your people
just didn't really want to handle it.

84
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:25,960
- Then I'll send--
- No need.

85
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:27,640
I'll handle it myself.

86
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:36,480
Why are you so desperate to get that land?
Is it because it used to belong to--

87
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:37,400
Sairung.

88
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:41,080
I already told you
never to mention that name again.

89
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,720
You don't want me saying her name,

90
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:47,800
but you're still trying to buy her land.
What exactly does that mean?

91
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:51,280
I'm a businessman.

92
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:54,440
If I see profit or benefit somewhere,
I go after it.

93
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:56,640
If you don't understand that,
then stay quiet.

94
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:59,880
Don't think or guess nonsense.
I don't like it.

95
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:16,280
May you be blessed
with long life, grace, happiness,

96
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,680
and strength.

97
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:26,640
Ms. Kaimook.

98
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:29,520
- Yes?
- Mr. Mek is asking for you.

99
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:30,840
Okay.

100
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:44,480
Did you need something, Dad?

101
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:49,680
Can I see
your underwater photography portfolio?

102
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:53,440
In all these years,
you've never asked to see it before.

103
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:56,240
Are you using it
as a reference for your planted tank?

104
00:20:56,320 --> 00:20:59,680
No. I'm thinking of using
the photos for next year's calendar.

105
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:01,360
Huh? A calendar?

106
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,760
Yeah. Why?

107
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:07,800
Nothing.
But I already sold all those photos.

108
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:12,480
You took plenty, didn't you?
Bring me the ones you haven't sold yet.

109
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:14,480
Yes.

110
00:21:56,880 --> 00:22:00,400
- Hello.
- Oh, Mr. Narathon. How've you been?

111
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,720
I'm good.

112
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:06,600
I didn't know you were into aquascaping.

113
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:12,400
Yes. I've been doing this for years.
Do you like it?

114
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:14,760
I do.

115
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:18,720
But I'm not skilled enough for it.

116
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:21,680
That's why I prefer diving
and photographing the real thing.

117
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,640
That's what I want to do.

118
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:27,200
Diving?

119
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:31,080
No. I want to build

120
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:35,320
a huge tank that looks
exactly like what you see underwater.

121
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:41,400
You mean an aquarium?

122
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:44,680
Exactly. A giant aquarium.

123
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:50,280
I'm going to call it "Coral World."

124
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,480
But I can't do it alone.
Would you help me?

125
00:22:57,960 --> 00:23:02,880
Sure. But I'm not sure
what I can help you with.

126
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:05,120
Whatever you're good at.

127
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,680
We'll take it step by step. No rush.

128
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:15,800
What are you two planning?

129
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:22,440
Something like this. But much bigger.

130
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:27,640
Do you think you can handle it?

131
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:34,640
Here, Dad. Underwater photos

132
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:35,880
that I actually managed to capture.

133
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:54,920
Amazing. Breeding rare marine species
for conservation like this.

134
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:57,160
I'd love to support it too.

135
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:59,000
Thank you.

136
00:23:59,720 --> 00:24:03,760
Besides releasing
some of them back into nature,

137
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:05,640
if it's not too much trouble,

138
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:09,440
don't forget about my Coral World project.

139
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:14,320
I want the aquarium I'm building
to feel alive.

140
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:17,720
A real ecosystem,
not just something pretty to look at.

141
00:24:20,080 --> 00:24:24,360
That's great.
People who can't swim or dive

142
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:26,800
will finally get to see another world too.

143
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:30,320
I'd be the first one.

144
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:34,640
Well, I'll lend you
Kaimook's photo albums.

145
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,720
Maybe it will inspire you.

146
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:39,160
Her photography is really interesting.

147
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:42,640
Of course.

148
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,240
Piak, go open the door.

149
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:30,280
- Who's that?
- Do you have a boat for rent?

150
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:36,120
Yes, but we're closed now.
Come back tomorrow.

151
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,040
Open the door.

152
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:43,960
The owner isn't here. Come back tomorrow.

153
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:46,960
Open, Pong. I'm not going to rob you.

154
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:05,320
Do you remember me?

155
00:26:21,440 --> 00:26:24,880
What are they hauling around
this late at night?

156
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:27,200
It's not your business. Go back to sleep.

157
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:31,720
Oh? Okay then. Good night.

158
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:34,040
See you tomorrow.

159
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,160
No.

160
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:54,240
Don't go.

161
00:26:58,160 --> 00:27:00,360
Look ahead.

162
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:04,120
Don't turn around.

163
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:17,360
The moment you look back, you'll all die.

164
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,160
Don't turn around.

165
00:27:55,720 --> 00:27:57,560
Hey, be careful.

166
00:28:05,320 --> 00:28:06,760
Are we almost there?

167
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:08,960
Yes.

168
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:11,040
Around here

169
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:14,080
there are a lot
of small islands and rocks.

170
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:17,120
Yes, there is more you can't see.

171
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:22,160
Good thing it's daytime. If it were
nighttime, nobody would dare come here.

172
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:28,360
We're almost there. Is everyone ready?

173
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:34,680
Bro, what are they going to do?

174
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:36,720
You don't need to know.

175
00:28:37,480 --> 00:28:40,680
Piak, if you see anything unusual,

176
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:42,640
don't say anything.

177
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:04,040
How was it?

178
00:29:04,120 --> 00:29:06,520
- All done.
- Good.

179
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:10,520
- What about the detonation system?
- All set. We just need to press it.

180
00:29:13,280 --> 00:29:15,800
Pong, where are we going to hide?

181
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:30,520
Hey, are they going to blow up the coral?

182
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:35,240
Yes. And if you're not going to shut up,
they're going to blow your head up too.

183
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:39,800
Ready.

184
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:16,000
Pong, go back there.

185
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:35,840
Piak, raise the anchor.

186
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:38,560
Oh? Why?

187
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:40,760
Just do it. Let's go back.

188
00:31:41,920 --> 00:31:43,960
Aren't we waiting for them to come back?

189
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:46,800
Just leave them here.

190
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:53,720
Are you sure they won't come back?

191
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:56,080
I don't think they'll make it back.

192
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,840
Please receive the blessing.

193
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:49,920
May you be blessed with long life,
grace, happiness, and strength.

194
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,200
<i>Sathu.</i>

195
00:32:53,880 --> 00:32:55,320
Venerable Sir.

196
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:58,120
What is it?

197
00:33:04,280 --> 00:33:05,160
Well…

198
00:33:08,600 --> 00:33:11,000
If we…

199
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:15,240
If we didn't mean to do wrong,

200
00:33:17,040 --> 00:33:18,560
it's not a sin, right?

201
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:22,320
It depends on your intention.

202
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:25,920
You must stay mindful at every moment,

203
00:33:26,440 --> 00:33:29,760
because these days, people do wrong

204
00:33:29,840 --> 00:33:33,040
both intentionally and unintentionally.

205
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:38,000
- Thank you.
- Bless you.

206
00:33:49,440 --> 00:33:51,480
Then please forgive me.

207
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:19,840
SAWANG RESCUE

208
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:39,880
Look! Look ahead.

209
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:43,679
Don't turn around.

210
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:52,400
The moment you look back, you die.

211
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:02,160
Look ahead. Don't look back.

212
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:06,440
Don't look. You'll die. Don't turn around.

213
00:36:02,920 --> 00:36:06,720
What is this? Why is there
water all over the place?

214
00:36:07,720 --> 00:36:09,520
Jang. Jang.

215
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:12,600
Come mop up the water now.

216
00:36:16,720 --> 00:36:18,720
These new maids are hopeless.

217
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:22,200
They didn't even mop up
the water outside the room.

218
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:23,760
I almost slipped.

219
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:25,640
They probably didn't see it.

220
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:30,320
You're too kind.
That's why they don't respect you.

221
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:34,080
How was the jewelry auction?

222
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:39,720
I thought the Heart of the Ocean
jewelry set would be up for auction.

223
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:43,000
But the owner changed her mind
and decided to keep it.

224
00:36:44,080 --> 00:36:45,600
So what did you get?

225
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:49,840
Nothing. I didn't like a single set.

226
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:51,640
Good.

227
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:55,280
What a waste of glam.

228
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,400
What are you looking at?

229
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:07,360
The photos I won at the auction.

230
00:37:09,920 --> 00:37:11,520
When will they send them over?

231
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:14,160
She said She's waiting for the professor
to finish grading them first.

232
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:18,000
Then she'll frame them in a style that
matches the photos. It'll take a while.

233
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:29,440
These photos actually look good.

234
00:37:30,040 --> 00:37:34,320
With the full set, when we resell them,
they'll probably fetch a good price.

235
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:39,000
You're interested in art now?

236
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:43,280
If it makes money

237
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:47,000
and makes me look better in society,

238
00:37:47,080 --> 00:37:48,800
I'll never back down.

239
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:51,360
You say that like you don't know me.

240
00:37:53,160 --> 00:37:56,920
I'll go call the maids to mop up
the water. Not sure if they're asleep now.

241
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:48,720
Mr. Phum.

242
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:51,600
How is it? Are you tired working here?

243
00:38:53,240 --> 00:38:54,320
No.

244
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:57,600
If you need anything, you can tell me.

245
00:38:59,160 --> 00:39:00,560
Okay. Thank you.

246
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:05,440
Hey.

247
00:39:08,360 --> 00:39:10,240
You'll get your face dirty.

248
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:35,280
How could something like this happen?

249
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:37,840
Who got you pregnant?

250
00:39:40,160 --> 00:39:42,200
I…

251
00:39:44,600 --> 00:39:45,880
Who got you pregnant?

252
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:49,480
I don't know.

253
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:54,440
How do you not know who you slept with?

254
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:00,280
If you don't tell me,

255
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:03,760
get out of my house right now.

256
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:06,920
And don't ever come back here again.

257
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:09,800
Rung, please.

258
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:13,120
Please let me stay.
Just give me some time.

259
00:40:13,200 --> 00:40:17,440
When I give birth, I'll leave.
Please, Rung.

260
00:40:17,520 --> 00:40:19,240
- Please.
- No.

261
00:40:20,840 --> 00:40:23,120
If you won't tell me who the father is,

262
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:26,280
you leave today.

263
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:34,680
Rung.

264
00:40:35,200 --> 00:40:36,440
Get out!

265
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:39,240
Please, Rung. I'm begging you.

266
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:41,320
I'm begging you.

267
00:40:53,520 --> 00:40:54,800
Mr. Phum.

268
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:01,960
I…

269
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:11,040
What do you want? Just tell me.

270
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:13,320
I can give you anything.

271
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:17,400
Well,

272
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:20,320
Mr. Phum. So…

273
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:26,360
I wanted to ask you…

274
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:30,160
What would you do if I got pregnant?

275
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:35,880
Don't, Sarai.

276
00:41:37,880 --> 00:41:40,480
You cannot get pregnant now.

277
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:46,360
Why? I thought you said you loved me.

278
00:41:47,760 --> 00:41:48,800
Yes.

279
00:41:49,400 --> 00:41:52,160
I do love you. More than anyone.

280
00:41:52,960 --> 00:41:55,000
But you can't get pregnant now.

281
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:59,080
If you get pregnant now,
you'll be in serious trouble.

282
00:42:01,040 --> 00:42:02,280
Why?

283
00:42:02,360 --> 00:42:04,480
Just listen to me.
You can't get pregnant yet.

284
00:42:05,600 --> 00:42:09,040
All you need to know is that I love you.

285
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:42,080
Or you ordered them to kill me?

286
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:49,320
I was loyal to you.

287
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:52,320
I did everything for you.

288
00:42:54,600 --> 00:42:56,080
But why?

289
00:42:57,200 --> 00:43:00,600
Why were you so cruel to me?

290
00:43:01,720 --> 00:43:02,680
Why?!

291
00:43:04,800 --> 00:43:06,080
Where did you

292
00:43:07,120 --> 00:43:09,600
take our child?

293
00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:16,520
Or did you…

294
00:43:18,640 --> 00:43:20,520
kill our child too?

295
00:43:22,080 --> 00:43:25,080
Mr. Phum, did you kill our child?!

296
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:27,280
Did you kill our child?!

297
00:43:35,280 --> 00:43:39,160
Because of that damn ghost,
everyone thinks I'm crazy.

298
00:43:39,240 --> 00:43:41,800
Because I can't contact anyone.

299
00:43:41,880 --> 00:43:43,680
I need your help.

300
00:43:43,760 --> 00:43:45,000
You have to help me!

301
00:43:49,400 --> 00:43:53,160
<i>I have a job for you.</i>
<i>Go search for Sarai's family treasure.</i>

302
00:43:55,360 --> 00:43:56,880
Keep this with you.

303
00:43:56,960 --> 00:44:00,240
That woman's spirit
won't be able to get close to you.

304
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:04,160
I'm interested
in the plot of land next to yours.

305
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:41,800
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
